<item>
            <title>[SPR-2326] Treat start/stop Lifecycle of beans like the init/destroy events</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2326</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Spring 2.0 now supports ApplicationContexts implementing the Lifecycle interface. I would like to see the start/stop functionality treated identically to that of init/destroy in the following way:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;sending of an ApplicationEvent after start and before stop&lt;br/&gt;
Currently init and destroy of ApplicationContexts send events as well. I would like to see this for start/stop too.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
